<span id="freeTextContainer10287067712888139207">Setting: Michigan, USA. Having really enjoyed Wreckage by this author, I was looking forward to this one - but was sadly disappointed with it:-<br/>Luke&apos;s wife Natalie has recently passed away after losing her battle with cancer at the age of 37, leaving Luke with three children to raise. From the day of the funeral, Luke begins to receive regular letters from Natalie, giving him advice on dealing with the children but also reminiscing on their past and her struggle with cancer. When eldest son Will </span>
  <span id="freeText10287067712888139207" style="display:none">Setting: Michigan, USA. Having really enjoyed Wreckage by this author, I was looking forward to this one - but was sadly disappointed with it:-<br />Luke's wife Natalie has recently passed away after losing her battle with cancer at the age of 37, leaving Luke with three children to raise. From the day of the funeral, Luke begins to receive regular letters from Natalie, giving him advice on dealing with the children but also reminiscing on their past and her struggle with cancer. When eldest son Will finds an envelope from an adoption agency in his mother's belongings, he questions whether he has been adopted. Assuring him he has not, Luke is still concerned about what his wife has been hiding from him and begins to investigate...<br />The book started slowly and was not especially gripping. It did get more interesting in the latter stages when Luke discovered what his wife had been hiding but an inconclusive ending totally let it down again. Only 6/10 for this one - hope her others are more like Wreckage as I have several on TBR!</span>
